				<IMG src="http://www.archspace.org/image/forum/posticon.gif" border=0>
				posted 2005-03-18 19:05&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;
				<A href="edit.php?board=sug&id=2172"><IMG alt="Edit/Delete Message" src="http://www.archspace.org/image/forum/edit.gif" border=0></A> 
			    <A href="reply.php?board=sug&id=2121"><IMG alt="Reply w/Quote" src="http://www.archspace.org/image/forum/quote.gif" border=0></A>
			    <HR color=#000000 SIZE=-1>
			  	During the current set I've changed my opinion a bit.  I still think privateering is fun as heck, and I even chose buckaneer for their privateering capabilities, but I am now agreeing with PoGo on this one.  Privateering is still fun for me, but at the moment in the grand scheme of things it does need to be &quot;made-over.&quot;  My suggestions are as follows:<br />
<br />
1.  PP and EXP gained are more proportional to privateer skills.  I see my level 16 (lone wolf) commander with plus 22 in privateer pulling down the same amount of gold as my lvl 3 commanders with 5 or 6 in privateer.  I believe at this point money gained is more proportional to money earned on the planets privateered on.  This is realistic, obviously, but make the extra ranks in privateer MEAN something.<br />
2.  I'd like to see privateering get a bit more creative.  A good privateer with big ships, for example, might not just steal money from enemy players.  If they see an opportunity they could board enemy ships stationed there and take them, intercept small research vessels, stealing RP (maybe our scientists can compare notes with theirs :D), and perhaps even ransack military bases stealing ships at the docks and MP.  Some of this, of course, could only be pulled off by the best privateers in the galaxy - but that ties into my first suggestion.<br />
3.  The benefits to privateering fleets as far as experience goes makes privateering hardly worth the risk.  Each time a privateer goes on a mission they risk dying, and gain very little experience each mission.  Even with the slight increase in commander experience privateering is almost a waste of time.  Also fleets who are privateering gain no experience (or if they gain some I haven't noticed).  A fleet on a privateer mission would learn about working together as a team, and get a feel for the navigation systems of their ships so I think it's realistic for them to gain a small amount of exp, even if it's just one or two per mission.<br />
<br />
Bugs/Problems/Questions<br />
<br />
Why do privateering fleets sometimes gain 0 PP?  If the planet has no production, such as planets with all military/research bases, they are going to need to get shipments from nearby planets for their upkeep, and those shipments can be intercepted.<br />
<br />
Why does it ever say &quot;This player has no more planets to privateer on&quot;?  Now, correct me if I'm wrong, but couldn't the fleets just go back to the first planet they privateered and keep privateering?<br />
<br />
Once I sent a fleet of frigates privateering.  14 frigates.  They got detected by a single fleet of gunboats and got shot down by that fleet.  Now hold on, I can see how maybe we were caught out of position and they got a few good shots at some of our ships, but the fleet of Patrol Boat MKI's somehow destroying my whole fleet stretches the imagination.<br />
<br />
That's all I got, I realize these changes will probably not take place since nobody really cares about privateering :D and this might take a bit of rewriting :S but I thought I'd at least get my thoughts out there.			   <P align=right></P>
			</TD>
		  </TR>

		
