				<IMG src="http://www.archspace.org/image/forum/posticon.gif" border=0>
				posted 2005-03-23 14:55&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;
				<A href="edit.php?board=sug&id=2193"><IMG alt="Edit/Delete Message" src="http://www.archspace.org/image/forum/edit.gif" border=0></A> 
			    <A href="reply.php?board=sug&id=2121"><IMG alt="Reply w/Quote" src="http://www.archspace.org/image/forum/quote.gif" border=0></A>
			    <HR color=#000000 SIZE=-1>
			  	I too hope privateers became more useful, I'm a Buckaneer and for the most part I find privateers very useless.  Now that I have better commanders I can expect to get 20k PP from a couple planets when privateering someone with around 20 planets, and having broken 100k once or twice, but I would be surprised if any one privateering mission averaged 30-40k per turn or more (when I get 40k+ from one planet the next 2-4 seem to give me less than 10K, often only in the hundreds :( ).  It isn't worth it when I'm making 750k+ PP in income and everytime I have done a fair amount of privateering I've eventually lost a fleet, and am lucky if I've made enough PP to replace that fleet, but a commander is also lost which IMO is worse.<br />
<br />
When I still do privateer I also get the &quot;Planet is already under privateering&quot; message a lot which means they spend a turn doing nothing - and a privateer rarely goes by that I don't get that message at about 50% of the planets my fleet &quot;visits.&quot;  I'm not certain, but I'm pretty sure my fleets have gone to the planets of one person multiple times, the first they privateer, the second visit they get the above message, and eventually they come home :(<br />
<br />
My suggestions about privateering - keeping it pretty much as is (ie stealing money) - however it would probably be overpowering since everyone can do it (ie it would work better for a pirate fleet).  Bear in mind I am not sure how privateering works currently.<br />
<br />
Base the PP gain largely off of the planets production, plus a bit that represents the commerce with other planets (exports).  How much of the planet's production is privateered depends on what you want privateering to do, as a Buckaneer I'd love to be able to make enough off of privateering that I have to put PP in the council to be distributed to others so I keep gaining PP and have few planets (other than my ship building would be really slow) - but this would make it too powerful especially if the &quot;better&quot; races could make a similarly large amount.  Taking the planets entire production, IMO, isn't that bad if it's used rarely (such as just Buckaneers and maybe humans - but that isn't how AS works).<br />
<br />
Assuming the fleet successfully privateers the planet, they get you a _maximum_ of X% of the planets production - I'm not certain what X should be, 20-25% might be fair, but I really have no clue.  Each ship has a maximum value it can carry - probably simplest to make it (space on the ship)*Y (ie a lone cruiser would be able to carry 940*Y PP away from the planet - and again I have no idea what the value of Y should be).  Small ships wouldn't be able to take away all of the PP they could probably, while dooms would probably have space left over.<br />
<br />
Ability:<br />
IMO the commander's privateer ability should be two fold:<br />
1. Increase the amount they can take away with them.  Either X or Y (or both, but that might be too much) could be increased.  If X were to increase, the commander strikes at the most opportune time - perhaps a convoy with exports is forming up, a convoy with imports has just arrived, the local fleets are preoccupied with something else, or the commander and his fleet have gotten very quick and efficient transferring the goods between ships/siezing the transports.<br />
<br />
If Y is increased it could be due to the ships having been refitted with larger/more cargo bays, stuffing the goods everywhere they fit, having learnt from experience to jam the goods into the cargo bays as efficiently as possible, or they carry more prize crews to commandeer transports.<br />
<br />
2. The second thing I think the privateer ability would be good for is survivability.  Chances are that a level 20 commander with a 20+ privateer ability would know the ropes and could slip by any defending fleets more easily.  Agerus and Buckaneers already have Stealth that does this, so adding a bit more probably wouldn't be hard.  The problem with balance would most likely be any Buckaneers that get their ending project would have 50% less chance of being detected _before_ this bonus.  Alternately, maybe the privateer is smart and runs when confronted (to save his fleet to live and fight another day).  Once the fleet _is_ detected, they have less chance of being damaged by the attacking fleet.  I am not sure if there are any modifiers already in place similar to this that could be slightly modified, if so it wouldn't be hard, otherwise it might be.<br />
<br />
&lt;dream mode: on&gt;<br />
A major modification to privateering would be interesting I think.<br />
<br />
Referring to Slayer's post:<br />
#1. I think the PP should be based on the planet's economy and the ship's privateering, with only minor increases for higher commander abilities.  Since I'm now thinking &quot;major overhaul of privateering,&quot; I don't think the experience should vary with the commander's ability to privateer because:<br />
<br />
#2. I love this idea.  Expanding privateering to RP and MP would make it a bit more interesting.  I suspect that the captured MP would be very low since you don't need all that much anyways.  I can see getting RP either fairly often in &quot;smaller&quot; quantities, or rarely, but when you do you get a lot of RP (smaller quantities means enough for lvl 2/3/4 techs, large quantities means enough for lvl 6/7/8/9 techs - but these amounts are probably too high).  Alternately make the privateer provide the information for a specific tech rather than RPs like stealing techs.  Gaining both RP (or techs) and MP should provide much more experience than PP - higher commander privateer ability increases the chance of it happening.<br />
Ransacking bases is a raid, so IMO that should not be included, but stealing ships in dock would be great.  The way I see it, the ship would need to be in the ship pool.  There would be a chance of any ship being on any given planets, more military bases would probably mean there's a greater chance of a ship (or multiple ships) being present.  This is where I think the privateer ability should really come into play.  A commander with a very high privateer ability should be able to take a warship away with a prize crew aboard.  The privateer ability not only increases the probability of this happening, but also the probability of the boarding action being more successful.<br />
There are two potential problems with this however - what if you have lvl 5-6 tech and you steal a teched out ship with HBH, DB, and OOD?  Do you gain these technologies? Just use them? Or can you not get them to work?  Secondly, for any tech level ship - you probably won't steal more than one at a time meaning you will only have one ship of that design.  It will need to be in a fleet of one unless you are lucky and manage to steal more of that design.  One way around this could be that you steal the ship hull, upon successfully returning to your empire you must select which design of that class the ship is (so it gets your level tech and weapons, and your choice of devices) or you can create a new design for the ship (in case you don't have a design for that ship class). This would be a huge experience boost for the commander - especially if you managed to steal a doomstar :)<br />
<br />
#3 Commanders gain 200 experience per planet, if you steal 25k or more (maybe 30k) you gain more experience.  I've gotten close to 600 once, but getting that much PP in the first place is a problem so I'm normally only getting 200 exp per planet.<br />
&lt;dream mode: off&gt;<br />
<br />
Unfortunately I doubt the devs think privateering is important enough for such a huge overhaul (I know I sure wouldn't want to have to code this LOL).			   <P align=right></P>
			</TD>
		  </TR>

		
