				<A href="edit.php?board=sug&id=2208"><IMG alt="Edit/Delete Message" src="http://www.archspace.org/image/forum/edit.gif" border=0></A> 
			    <A href="reply.php?board=sug&id=2121"><IMG alt="Reply w/Quote" src="http://www.archspace.org/image/forum/quote.gif" border=0></A>
			    <HR color=#000000 SIZE=-1>
			  	Everyone knows privateering is pretty much useless, payouts of 100k+ PP from a single planet are fairly rare, with a lot of planets providing 0-20k or so.<br />
<br />
I privateered three people in the last few days and kept track of what planets they visited, and whether they made any PP or not from their visit.  Combined the three privateer missions attempted to privateer 73 planets - of those 73 planets however, 30 (41%) were repeat visits that were just a waste of time.  What's worse, one privateer mission went to the same planet four times before returning (only making any PP and gaining experience from the first visit), and another privateered the same planet _THREE TIMES IN A ROW_.  How stupid are these commanders?  It could be expected they'd do something stupid once or twice, then they'd realize they can't privateer the same planet twice in one mission.<br />
<br />
Since privateering is rarely used, and even when done with a level 20 commander with dooms it's not worth the time or risk, could something be done about the stupidity of the commanders?<br />
<br />
The two simple ways to make privateering still useless, but not have the commanders be stupid are to:<br />
1. allow privateering the same planet multiple times in one mission.<br />
<br />
or<br />
<br />
2. make commanders a bit smarter so they don't go back to a planet they've already privateered.			   <P align=right></P>
